25/03/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Montenegro and the EU signed an agreement Wednesday (March 24th) on the participation of Montenegrin troops in the ATALANTA naval operation, which combats piracy off the Somali coast. 
The document was signed in Brussels by Montenegro's military representative to NATO and the EU, Ljubisa Jokic, and Robert Cooper, EU director-general for External and Political-Military Affairs. 
(RTCG, Cafemontenegro - 24/03/10)
